<p><b>Yukio Mishima</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">三島 由紀夫</span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_comma" style="display:none">,</span><i><span class="t_nihongo_romaji">Mishima Yukio</span></i><span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> was the pseudonym of <b>Kimitake Hiraoka</b> <span style="font-weight: normal">(<span class="t_nihongo_kanji"><span lang="ja" xml:lang="ja">平岡 公威</span></span> <span class="t_nihongo_comma" style="display:none">,</span><i><span class="t_nihongo_romaji">Hiraoka Kimitake</span></i><span class="t_nihongo_help noprint"><sup><a href="/wiki/Help:Japanese" title="Help:Japanese"><span class="t_nihongo_icon" style="color: #00e; font: bold 80% sans-serif; text-decoration: none; padding: 0 .1em;">?</span></a></sup></span>, January 14, 1925–November 25, 1970)</span>, a <a href="/wiki/Japanese_people" title="Japanese people">Japanese</a> author, poet and playwright.</p>
